# PAM service for Hermes consent gates — the SINGLE device-password check.
# Used by every "human consent" surface (remote-access disable, etc.) so there
# is ONE password (the device account password set at onboarding, in /etc/shadow)
# verified ONE way everywhere.
#
# Minimal on purpose: only pam_unix (password vs /etc/shadow, supports yescrypt
# via libcrypt). NO pam_securetty / pam_nologin / pam_systemd — those require a
# tty / login session and FAIL inside a systemd oneshot (which is where the
# verification runs as root). That tty requirement is exactly why service="login"
# misbehaves in a non-interactive context.
auth     required   pam_unix.so
account  required   pam_unix.so
